The Senator Representing Sokoto East, Dr. Ibrahim Abdullahi Gobir (APC), has distributed over N40million worth of food items  to his constituents. The items included rice, sugar and millet, Bello Mohammed Anka,a media aide to the Senator disclosed. Mohammed, who stated this yesterday in Sokoto, said the gesture was for this year’s Ramadan and to cushion effect of measures against coronavirus. At the flag off of the distribution, the lawmaker explained that the gesture was to  assist the electorate with provisions to  break their fast and enable them to comply with the directive to  stay at home following the coronavirus pandemic, Mohammed said. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here  COVID-19: Constituents lament neglect by lawmakers as lockdown bites harder Ramadan: Senator Maccido donates to PDP constituents 1000 households get palliatives from Niger East lawmaker